@DandelionSprout Hello..? I'm closing the issue right now. Because of your non-response to the mail and comment on this issue. Feel free to add a comment if you want to reopen. Then, I will open.

> [!NOTE]
> The issue is marked as “A: Waiting for data”. It will be closed in 5 days if there’s no new activity.

> The current rules in that section don't fix the above issue. I'll move the rule to that part.

I was just pointing out that it should be in the Rogers Media section. I also noticed this rule still matches: `||utility.rogersmedia.com/utility.js$script,redirect=noopjs,domain=`. I didn't look into what it's used for, however.

Edit: I took a quick look, and it appears to be used for ads.

